text: Wesley H. Coffyn (August 7, 1878 – November 27, 1946) was a Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick as member of the Conservative party representing Gloucester County from 1931 to 1935. ==References== Category:20th-century Canadian politicians Category:1878 births Category:1947 deaths Category:Progressive Conservative Party of New Brunswick MLAs
